line_1: The heavy Wall climb'd slowly after
line_2: Aloft rose ev'ry Beam and Rafter,

line_1: Was found some twenty Ages after:
line_2: Tea, says a Critic big with Laughter,

line_1: One can't imagine what he's after:
line_2: Remarks, that so provoke one's Laughter,

line_1: And makes one look so foolish after,
line_2: Fit subject or of scorn or laughter;
